2026-04-21 02:38:03 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Control module 1 switch indicator LED/resistor circuit', 'Control module 2 switch indicator LED/resistor circuit', 'Control module 3 switch indicator LED/resistor circuit', 'Control module 4 switch indicator LED/resistor circuit', 'Control module 5 switch indicator LED/resistor circuit', 'Control module 6 switch indicator LED/resistor circuit', 'Control module 7 switch indicator LED/resistor circuit', 'Control module 8 switch indicator LED/resistor circuit'] hypothesis_explanation='All red switch indicator LEDs and their series resistors are physically missing from each control module, leaving an open circuit in every indicator LED branch in parallel with each switch, but all switches are ON. With all switches closed, their respective indicator branches (even if open) should not affect the series path of the 12V from supply to the load. However, the described system behavior (no load lamp) and confirmed cable connection and switch closure imply that the absence of every LED/resistor branch (not just failed LEDs but missing physical components, creating open circuits) could indicate these components were providing the primary current path in the physical implementation (contrary to schematic intent), or there are additional faults that were not revealed in tests. Based on reported findings, the physical absence of all switch indicators and their resistors is the single clear anomaly that fully distinguishes the current state from normal operation.'
